      {
        "id": 2209166,
        "name": "Merrill Lindquist",
        "username": "Merrill_Lindquist",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/merrill_lindquist/{size}/884_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-06-28T00:21:21.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Who do they list as winemaker and/or consulting winemaker? The vineyard is stellar, managed very well, and I have not seen any changes in the vineyard (from the street - they are neighbors). I thought Francoise Peschon was still at the helm there.</p>\n<p>Chateau Latour purchased the operation a few years ago, kept the name Araujo for some time, but now, thankfully, have returned the label to Eisele Vibeyard.</p>",
