      {
        "id": 2209251,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-06-28T02:27:51.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The winemaker is now H\u00e9l\u00e8ne Mignot, with input from the rest of the Pinault team, inc. Latour\u2019s winemaker (or more accurately, technical director), also named H\u00e9l\u00e8ne (Genin).</p>\n<p>I think she\u2019s doing a great job. The blend is now based on which blocks have the best terroir (deep, gravel / cobble soils), as opposed to being crafted for immediate impact; we\u2019ll see what effect that has down the line. More noticeable is superior oak integration compared with the old r\u00e9gime. I\u2019ve also noted (at least perceptibly) brighter acidity.</p>\n<p>They are also about to replant some of the Syrah parcels, which the team believe were not optimally sited.</p>\n<p>All in all I think the two Cabernet cuv\u00e9es are great, better than under the Araujos\u2014but I haven\u2019t tasted the Syrah, so can\u2019t comment on that.</p>",
